Aim
To perform vulnerability scanning on a target system using Nessus Essentials and analyze detected
vulnerabilities based on severity levels.
Introduction
Nessus Essentials is a vulnerability assessment tool used to identify security weaknesses in systems,
networks, and web applications. It scans target machines and detects vulnerabilities such as outdated
software, open ports, weak configurations, and security risks.
Nessus categorizes vulnerabilities into:
• Critical
• High
• Medium
• Low
• Informational
It is widely used in cybersecurity and penetration testing for security auditing and risk assessment.
Procedure
Step 1: Download Nessus Essentials
1. Open browser and visit the Nessus official website.
2. Download Nessus Essentials for Windows.
Step 2: Install Nessus
1. Run the installer.
2. Complete the installation process.
Step 3: Open Nessus Interface
Open browser and access:
https://localhost:8834
Step 4: Register Nessus
1. Create/login Tenable account.
2. Obtain activation code.
3. Enter the activation key in Nessus setup.
Step 5: Configure Nessus
1. Wait for plugin download and initialization.
2. Open Nessus dashboard.
Step 6: Create New Scan
1. Click New Scan.
2. Select Basic Network Scan.
Step 7: Configure Target
Enter:
• Scan name
• Target IP address or domain
Example:
www.grace.edu.in
Step 8: Launch Scan
Click Launch to begin vulnerability scanning.
Step 9: Analyze Results
Observe:
• Open ports
• Vulnerabilities
• Severity levels
• Service information
